    <node id="625">
      <data key="d0">625</data>
      <data key="d1">data</data>
      <data key="d2">625 is a nominal designation used in the pressure-temperature ratings table. It represents a specific data point and can denote either a temperature point or a pressure class within this table. Specifically, 625°C is a temperature point listed in the table, indicating a temperature value of 625 degrees Celsius. Additionally, 625 is described as a numerical value representing a specific data point in a series. Overall, it serves as a reference for identifying particular conditions in the pressure-temperature ratings table.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-60e2c03b70ebe59caed656860d1a9d96&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-e08aa81b5449d47c5a323ae8a58ce735&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-3d70c5f8f778994cad7edb7ef10f4635&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-685be4db70f3b18d8a8fac56db2cfaa3&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-79c91ff40c85bc2676ba1a4dead29f2a&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-65a7f7e9599ea4d5c1cfc7d449c5a081&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-2879e8ce1f305f975a2bf33f2d701842&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-603423286a04ee8b6cbcba90c6a2736a&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-8320960a6b13ba4e9b766f5cfbdd1e80</data>
      <data key="d4">ASME B16.5-2013.pdf</data>
