      <data key="d2">325°C is a temperature point in the pressure–temperature ratings table.&lt;SEP&gt;325 is a specific pressure class.&lt;SEP&gt;325°C is a temperature point listed in the table.&lt;SEP&gt;325 is a pressure class in the table.&lt;SEP&gt;325°C is a temperature point in the pressure-temperature ratings table.&lt;SEP&gt;325 is a pressure value in pounds per square inch gauge (psig).&lt;SEP&gt;325 is a numerical data point.</data>
