    <node id="Copyright ASME International">
      <data key="d0">Copyright ASME International</data>
      <data key="d1">concept</data>
      <data key="d2">Copyright ASME International indicates the copyright holder of the document.&lt;SEP&gt;Copyright ASME International indicates the copyright notice for the ASME B16.5-2013 standard.&lt;SEP&gt;Copyright indicates the legal protection of the ASME B16.5-2013 standard document.&lt;SEP&gt;Copyright ASME International indicates the legal rights and permissions for the document.&lt;SEP&gt;Copyright ASME International indicates the intellectual property rights of ASME International over the document.&lt;SEP&gt;Copyright ASME International indicates the licensing agreement for the ASME B16.5-2013 standard.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-d0f2fde18096ae54093e820b71568eac&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-cfef247a2504069e002ce01be642a1e9&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-824f6bfcd2b200f81ced17dd1feea1ae&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-f024c3dde67312e25d76e977dcb7753c&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-0fe5be51acec68fed955f28940bdb235&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-ac011d5da9f248ab56440661b906cb38&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-94cdf656dce585522668d44a215fd0dd</data>
      <data key="d4">ASME B16.5-2013.pdf</data>
      <data key="d5">1776329032</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Bore">
      <data key="d0">Bore</data>
      <data key="d1">concept</data>
      <data key="d2">Bore refers to the internal diameter of pipes or fittings, particularly in the context of welding neck flanges.&lt;SEP&gt;Bore is the internal diameter of a pipe or pipe fitting.&lt;SEP&gt;Bore refers to the inside diameter of a pipe or tube.&lt;SEP&gt;Bore is a measurement of the inside diameter of the pipe flange as detailed in ASME B16.5-2013.&lt;SEP&gt;Bore is a term used to describe the internal diameter of a pipe or tube.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-5710fd22abab3effd14cb3f3d4187858&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-c5f5e2c6bb85dac52bdfa7453796ec77&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-5e85bee1a6414b667d34d9e3ddb49f16&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-cbee673be506ab63f82af3e68ebebcd1&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-90c280892e81306b9d7b1a397e54f308</data>
      <data key="d4">ASME B16.5-2013.pdf</data>
      <data key="d5">1776329032</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Ring Joint">
      <data key="d0">Ring Joint</data>
      <data key="d1">artifact</data>
      <data key="d2">Ring Joint is a type of flanged fitting commonly used in pipe fittings and piping systems. It involves a ring groove machined into one pipe and a corresponding ring inserted to create a secure seal. This type of joint is specifically described in the ASME B16.5-2013 standard, which also mentions it in the context of Class 150 Flanged Fittings. Ring Joint is a specific form of flanged joint designed to ensure a reliable seal, often utilizing a ring gasket for sealing purposes. It is a method of joining pipes and fittings, serving as a component in various industrial applications where precise and durable connections are required.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-8141fd83406f7d50dac6f93c308cba1a&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-02c8f43c223cee2154c66d0d4ab324af&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-2c1e39e4ae6c4190629baeb4a23e7884&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-87960735c6e595f042bd664132512ec0&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-20a6e7f0600d773fff6396f54c63b132&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-824f6bfcd2b200f81ced17dd1feea1ae&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-711c2dd0d5dd4ddd0ed3c6d027a7e27c&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-e8e222332c639c6f676a804e40276271&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-de39ca8c7c360d8542b6e7b848f32671&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-2cfed12e16e2f62a0ac34d806ce49eea&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-4313edccf5db74352d91e3f18890a0a0&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-f17e2ea5f154e082324b9ac9b148a73e&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-5fd12d8684f80d487e4f8acfca82848a&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-745a7a353b1e1e00489d9e9aa987acd1&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-7d620a92f42ccd64b2c87242914a0398&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-97f26dc410df4f859afb6e6e5370b13e&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-1d0f7d26ba441435e49ef6d46820f716</data>
      <data key="d4">ASME B16.5-2013.pdf</data>
      <data key="d5">1776329032</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Welding Neck Flange">
      <data key="d0">Welding Neck Flange</data>
      <data key="d1">artifact</data>
      <data key="d2">Welding Neck Flange is a type of flange with a necked section that allows for welding to a pipe.&lt;SEP&gt;Welding Neck Flange is a type of flange described in ASME B16.5-2013.&lt;SEP&gt;Welding neck flange is a type of flange with a reduced bore and a neck that allows for welding.&lt;SEP&gt;Welding Neck Flange is a type of flange with a neck for welding.&lt;SEP&gt;Welding neck flange is a type of flange where the neck is welded to the pipe.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-5710fd22abab3effd14cb3f3d4187858&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-cbee673be506ab63f82af3e68ebebcd1&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-4a2aa51a49817516d8e488a9d7c544a9&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-de39ca8c7c360d8542b6e7b848f32671&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-e253e99ebed9a87e642e60132b8f53d9</data>
      <data key="d4">ASME B16.5-2013.pdf</data>
      <data key="d5">1776329032</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Backing Ring Contact Surface">
      <data key="d0">Backing Ring Contact Surface</data>
      <data key="d1">artifact</data>
      <data key="d2">Backing Ring Contact Surface is a specific part of a welding neck flange where a backing ring contacts.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-5710fd22abab3effd14cb3f3d4187858</data>
      <data key="d4">ASME B16.5-2013.pdf</data>
      <data key="d5">1776329032</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Reducer">
      <data key="d0">Reducer</data>
      <data key="d1">artifact</data>
      <data key="d2">Reducer is a type of pipe fitting that connects pipes of different diameters. It is specifically designed to reduce the nominal pipe size and is often used in plumbing and industrial applications. Reducers are mentioned in the ASME B16.5-2013 standard, which provides detailed specifications and dimensions for these fittings. These fittings can also be flanged, meaning they have法兰连接，用于连接不同直径的管道。它们通常在给排水和工业应用中使用，并且在ASME B16.5-2013标准中有详细的规定和尺寸说明。此外，描述还提到减压器是一种符合特定尺寸规范的管件类型。</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-366d21bccd71c76a4c780fde0cfa7e08&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-02c8f43c223cee2154c66d0d4ab324af&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-ccbc09bef8fd93e5314dec1dbec481cb&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-8e7b456ed825c2e777586a3d95199f23&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-20a6e7f0600d773fff6396f54c63b132&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-439097792cec97ce9b1b0fb080fa39fc&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-2cfed12e16e2f62a0ac34d806ce49eea&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-57eadb61afc03dbca89ec4177318d30f&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-5fd12d8684f80d487e4f8acfca82848a&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-bca2cf22c89695d4ce65335b23352b32&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-ee003a76b54c8fcc7f20010252b7e38c</data>
      <data key="d4">ASME B16.5-2013.pdf</data>
      <data key="d5">1776329032</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="ASME International">
      <data key="d0">ASME International</data>
      <data key="d1">organization</data>
      <data key="d2">ASME International is a professional organization that develops and publishes standards for engineering and technology, including the ASME B16.5-2013 standard. It is responsible for providing and maintaining the standards and guidelines for various aspects of engineering and related fields, such as the pressure-temperature ratings for different materials and the specifications for pipe fitting dimensions. ASME International also acts as the copyright holder for the documents it publishes, including the ASME B16.5-2013 standard document and other related tables and material specifications. Additionally, it provides certifications and governs the standards mentioned in the text, ensuring that the guidelines and practices in engineering adhere to its established criteria.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-366d21bccd71c76a4c780fde0cfa7e08&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-d0f2fde18096ae54093e820b71568eac&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-e08aa81b5449d47c5a323ae8a58ce735&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-91fb20c66854d4220d2bb89dece25b26&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-02c8f43c223cee2154c66d0d4ab324af&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-c5f5e2c6bb85dac52bdfa7453796ec77&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-e6dd99d0d594bbdd5db11e31461478c9&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-8c9531d076f004c30f7355a51c50bbeb&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-920ee37a2f41f0148b3f2c484edae395&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-1261f13c12701dc16f49237f702e1cab&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-2c1e39e4ae6c4190629baeb4a23e7884&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-7d361c91bf3e9c4f81478ff64f43f6fa&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-9010b0d631cf0ee8f2876c69fd7db43d&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-69f5dfdb3c7a4f92fcc61b0351584206&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-8e7b456ed825c2e777586a3d95199f23&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-376c9d90c67ab8cb5f4d7bef0d9995e3&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-e5e7d6611dd06e592bef62dbd08dc044&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-c1c1f70080d9d2a6ea93b5640ca8cea0&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-e8f5c9d7666d5ca64fad9fe5409f4a67&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-a3453de580e274b0494108b0ff7189ee&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-bbc4f25f5a21132e1571d8baa298136c&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-caecc4edbb295cee17a2e0533066f3b0&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-8c26f486bf229ab399297201ce84ec2f&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-f67cfb71cad6bdaadc291b0dfadb7d87&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-fb7c5babdbcd75bdf9752cd67bcadc21&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-cfef247a2504069e002ce01be642a1e9&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-4303e33e6d61d4207aeb4ef2e5ef35ea&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-0def5c7323fd1839a8729ecb6b306f46&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-585c1c45925ddd2546b76b97e57456ed&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-47d30b91c8304767d9ee5dee433bb6cd&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-cbee673be506ab63f82af3e68ebebcd1&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-d88c25523fb6a395eb9e2724eb0719d5&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-83ab283e30659c933554a033613d2618&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-bc5fbf3f97e8bcfd2b79a4ca1deaa326&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-685be4db70f3b18d8a8fac56db2cfaa3&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-b16d82598801637712b84cc1424040fd&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-1873d06e9a30c27b355fbcaa093fe77d&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-5c8a2582fdf55b244cf7d4892e61cc9f&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-4a2aa51a49817516d8e488a9d7c544a9&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-de39ca8c7c360d8542b6e7b848f32671&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-82774a230daae