    <node id="Raised Face">
      <data key="d0">Raised Face</data>
      <data key="d1">concept</data>
      <data key="d2">Raised Face is a specific design feature of an artifact, particularly a type of surface finish for pipe fittings. It is also a type of flange with a raised surface, often mentioned in the context of pipe fittings. According to the ASME B16.5-2013 standard, Raised Face is a specific type of flange face that provides a raised surface for sealing purposes. This design involves the flange protruding above the nominal diameter of the pipe, making it a crucial element in ensuring proper sealing and functionality in pipe systems. The Raised Face design is a type of flange face configuration described in various standard documents, emphasizing its importance in the field of pipe fittings and flange manufacturing.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-366d21bccd71c76a4c780fde0cfa7e08&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-02c8f43c223cee2154c66d0d4ab324af&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-1d52749554047f9105f29ff3d1b53ac5&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-87960735c6e595f042bd664132512ec0&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-824f6bfcd2b200f81ced17dd1feea1ae&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-de39ca8c7c360d8542b6e7b848f32671&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-2cfed12e16e2f62a0ac34d806ce49eea&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-57eadb61afc03dbca89ec4177318d30f&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-bca2cf22c89695d4ce65335b23352b32&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-ee003a76b54c8fcc7f20010252b7e38c&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-97f26dc410df4f859afb6e6e5370b13e&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-eb33e5534b0b007ab3fc536bdf30e65c&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-40e7dd88714557fcaa5b58340393bd06</data>
