    <node id="600">
      <data key="d0">600</data>
      <data key="d1">data</data>
      <data key="d2">600 is a temperature point in the pressure-temperature ratings table, specifically listed in degrees Celsius as 600°C. This temperature range is applicable for certain material groups and pressure classes. Additionally, 600 is a nominal designation for a material in the pressure-temperature ratings table and a specific data point within this table. It also serves as a working pressure class in the ASME B16.5-2013 standard document, where it corresponds to 600 psi at 400°F for the 72Ni–15Cr–8Fe B564 Gr. N06600 material. Furthermore, 600 is a numerical value representing a specific data point and a specific dimension value for ring-joint facings.</data>
