    <node id="Class">
      <data key="d0">Class</data>
      <data key="d1">concept</data>
      <data key="d2">Class is a concept used in pressure-temperature ratings, denoting different categories or classes. These classes are represented in tables and refer to working pressure classes, pressure classes listed or specified for materials under various temperature conditions, and pressure-temperature rating classes. Class categorizes materials based on their performance at specific pressure and temperature levels, ensuring safe and reliable operation in different environments.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-96c734977fc84cffaf22fdd39ee3ed1b&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-8c9531d076f004c30f7355a51c50bbeb&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-c1c1f70080d9d2a6ea93b5640ca8cea0&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-cfef247a2504069e002ce01be642a1e9&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-d9d6f8ad3531ac0840bf5ba01dc89ab8&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-f9faa893029db6f5b871493c6380ddac&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-2879e8ce1f305f975a2bf33f2d701842&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-30fa107e1afe5b6cba81caa3af7a1ab4&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-8a7f9dd013cfda7208dab84e4831ce4a</data>
