    <node id="1500">
      <data key="d0">1500</data>
      <data key="d1">data</data>
      <data key="d2">1500°C is a specific temperature point in the pressure-temperature ratings table. This temperature is applicable for certain material groups and pressure classes. Additionally, 1500 is recognized as a working pressure class in the ASME B16.5-2013 standard document. While primarily associated with temperature, 1500 also represents a specific dimension value for ring-joint facings.</data>
