    <node id="400">
      <data key="d0">400</data>
      <data key="d1">data</data>
      <data key="d2">400°C is a temperature point listed in the pressure-temperature ratings table. This temperature is applicable for certain material groups and pressure classes. Additionally, 400 is a specific temperature in degrees Celsius and a working pressure class in the ASME B16.5-2013 standard document. It also represents a numerical value in a series and a specific data point. The temperature 400°C corresponds to 300°F, which is the working pressure for the 72Ni–15Cr–8Fe B564 Gr. N06600 material.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-44664e1f68bc892f4b7b0a535c4414b7&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-e08aa81b5449d47c5a323ae8a58ce735&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-335c2335ba413830aae1a70244aa5a26&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-fb7c5babdbcd75bdf9752cd67bcadc21&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-94e58312a7e84066f13cc4e7ad9465d9&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-83ab283e30659c933554a033613d2618&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-685be4db70f3b18d8a8fac56db2cfaa3&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-1873d06e9a30c27b355fbcaa093fe77d&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-f9faa893029db6f5b871493c6380ddac&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-65a7f7e9599ea4d5c1cfc7d449c5a081&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-2879e8ce1f305f975a2bf33f2d701842&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-603423286a04ee8b6cbcba90c6a2736a&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-30fa107e1afe5b6cba81caa3af7a1ab4&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-4bf1cc2e275f250252f3766b12889d76</data>
