    <node id="900">
      <data key="d0">900</data>
      <data key="d1">data</data>
      <data key="d2">900°C is a specific temperature point in the pressure-temperature ratings table, applicable for certain material groups and pressure classes. This temperature is also mentioned as a working pressure class in the ASME B16.5-2013 standard document. While 900 is referred to as a temperature point in various contexts, it is notably associated with a working pressure of 900 psi at 600°F for the 72Ni–15Cr–8Fe B564 Gr. N06600 material. These descriptions collectively highlight the significance of 900°C as a critical temperature marker in industrial applications, particularly concerning material performance and pressure ratings.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-44664e1f68bc892f4b7b0a535c4414b7&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-335c2335ba413830aae1a70244aa5a26&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-fb7c5babdbcd75bdf9752cd67bcadc21&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-94e58312a7e84066f13cc4e7ad9465d9&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-83ab283e30659c933554a033613d2618&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-1873d06e9a30c27b355fbcaa093fe77d&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-f9faa893029db6f5b871493c6380ddac&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-65a7f7e9599ea4d5c1cfc7d449c5a081&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-2879e8ce1f305f975a2bf33f2d701842&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-4bf1cc2e275f250252f3766b12889d76</data>
      <data key="d4">ASME B16.5-2013.pdf</data>
      <data key="d5">1776329037</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
