    </node>
    <node id="Eccentric Reducers">
      <data key="d0">Eccentric Reducers</data>
      <data key="d1">artifact</data>
      <data key="d2">Eccentric Reducers are a type of fitting mentioned in the document.&lt;SEP&gt;Eccentric Reducers are reducers where the axis of the smaller pipe is offset from the axis of the larger pipe.&lt;SEP&gt;Eccentric reducers are a specific type of reducer and are detailed in paragraphs 6.2.3 and 6.4.2.2.&lt;SEP&gt;Eccentric Reducers are fittings that reduce the size of pipes and have specific dimensions as described in the document.&lt;SEP&gt;Eccentric reducers are specific components mentioned in technical specifications.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-ccbc09bef8fd93e5314dec1dbec481cb&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-9010b0d631cf0ee8f2876c69fd7db43d&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-439097792cec97ce9b1b0fb080fa39fc&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-1a18d7afa11aad3756a7707e009d78fc&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-eb33e5534b0b007ab3fc536bdf30e65c</data>
      <data key="d4">ASME B16.5-2013.pdf</data>
      <data key="d5">1776329037</data>
