    </node>
    <node id="Straight Sizes">
      <data key="d0">Straight Sizes</data>
      <data key="d1">concept</data>
      <data key="d2">Straight sizes refer to standard pipe diameters without reductions.&lt;SEP&gt;Straight Sizes are a category of dimensions mentioned in the document.&lt;SEP&gt;Straight Sizes refer to standard dimensions applicable to fittings without reductions.&lt;SEP&gt;Straight sizes are applicable for certain dimensions and are detailed in paragraphs 6.2.3 and 6.4.2.2.&lt;SEP&gt;Straight Sizes refer to the standard sizes of fittings mentioned in the document.&lt;SEP&gt;Straight sizes refer to a category of dimensions in technical specifications.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-ccbc09bef8fd93e5314dec1dbec481cb&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-9010b0d631cf0ee8f2876c69fd7db43d&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-439097792cec97ce9b1b0fb080fa39fc&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-b8d7fbf71d349a93ea469c5166b31e89&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-1a18d7afa11aad3756a7707e009d78fc&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-eb33e5534b0b007ab3fc536bdf30e65c</data>
