    <node id="425°C">
      <data key="d0">425°C</data>
      <data key="d1">temperature</data>
      <data key="d2">425°C is a temperature threshold for certain materials, beyond which specific phase conversions may occur.&lt;SEP&gt;425°C is a temperature threshold beyond which certain materials may undergo phase changes. Specifically, steel carbide may convert to graphite.&lt;SEP&gt;425°C is the temperature threshold above which certain steel materials may undergo phase conversion.&lt;SEP&gt;425°C is a temperature threshold mentioned in the notes for material usage guidelines.&lt;SEP&gt;425°C is the temperature limit for the use of certain materials.&lt;SEP&gt;425°C is the maximum temperature limit for using Solution Annealed Material.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-c1c1f70080d9d2a6ea93b5640ca8cea0&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-a3453de580e274b0494108b0ff7189ee&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-caecc4edbb295cee17a2e0533066f3b0&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-82774a230daae46ca5bfd3f0231302b9&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-fe557ad0e335444e461df848f9e28d6b&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-fffc9136a01f33dba4c5242dae862755</data>
