    <node id="Flange">
      <data key="d0">Flange</data>
      <data key="d1">artifact</data>
      <data key="d2">Flange is a component used to connect pipes or fittings, often with a raised rim to seal against the pipe. This circular plate or rim is typically found at the end of a pipe and is essential in the fabrication of flanged fittings. Flanges are specified by nominal size (NPS) and are detailed in standards such as ASME B16.5-2013, where they are classified according to different classes, including Class 300. These components are integral to piping systems, facilitating connections between pipes and other fittings. The dimensions of flanges are provided in relevant tables, ensuring precise and standardized connections.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-5710fd22abab3effd14cb3f3d4187858&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-37388fa1515f3cf7a8930b2598d5740e&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-c5f5e2c6bb85dac52bdfa7453796ec77&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-87960735c6e595f042bd664132512ec0&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-c51efac4fa55567bbc6ceb90ad47bc5d&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-439097792cec97ce9b1b0fb080fa39fc&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-b181980b1dcef22dc859d6b6b9c724e1&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-97992c13bd15395adccdb59249057965&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-5e85bee1a6414b667d34d9e3ddb49f16&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-b8d7fbf71d349a93ea469c5166b31e89&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-4a2aa51a49817516d8e488a9d7c544a9&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-1359b097a2ba15f87aae6ad689a2a7a9&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-2cfed12e16e2f62a0ac34d806ce49eea&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-5fd12d8684f80d487e4f8acfca82848a&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-e253e99ebed9a87e642e60132b8f53d9&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-bca2cf22c89695d4ce65335b23352b32&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-4151555a834c7ca05d4e5d3bd1722dbb&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-eb33e5534b0b007ab3fc536bdf30e65c&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-40e7dd88714557fcaa5b58340393bd06&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-2c1e39e4ae6c4190629baeb4a23e7884</data>
      <data key="d4">ASME B16.5-2013.pdf</data>
      <data key="d5">1776329039</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
