    <node id="Hub">
      <data key="d0">Hub</data>
      <data key="d1">artifact</data>
      <data key="d2">Hub is a central part of a flange that connects to a pipe. This component is crucial for providing a mounting surface for connecting pipes or other flanges. Hub dimensions and tolerances are specified in the ASME B16.5-2013 standard, which also includes tables detailing these specifications. The hub is described as the core around which the flange is constructed, and it is associated with bevel angles and dimensions relevant to flange construction. These dimensions and specific characteristics are further elaborated upon in the standard, ensuring precise manufacturing and installation processes.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-5710fd22abab3effd14cb3f3d4187858&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-c5f5e2c6bb85dac52bdfa7453796ec77&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-2c1e39e4ae6c4190629baeb4a23e7884&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-4303e33e6d61d4207aeb4ef2e5ef35ea&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-97992c13bd15395adccdb59249057965&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-5e85bee1a6414b667d34d9e3ddb49f16&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-47d30b91c8304767d9ee5dee433bb6cd&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-4a2aa51a49817516d8e488a9d7c544a9&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-e253e99ebed9a87e642e60132b8f53d9&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-c5ace9ce39146c54679f4e19c3434a59&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-9480b43d18d635d04248ae532bf3633c</data>
      <data key="d4">ASME B16.5-2013.pdf</data>
      <data key="d5">1776329039</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="NPS">
      <data key="d0">NPS</data>
      <data key="d1">concept</data>
      <data key="d2">NPS stands for Nominal Pipe Size, a standard designation used in the measurement and identification of pipe, flange, or flanged fitting end connection sizes. This concept is widely recognized in the industry for its role in ensuring consistent and standardized measurements across various applications. NPS is defined in the ASME B16.5-2013 document, which provides detailed specifications for pipe dimensions and flange sizes. While NPS is often associated with pipe diameters, it also encompasses the sizing of pipe fittings and flanges. It is important to note that there is some variation in terminology, with NPS sometimes being referred to as National Pipe Size or National Pipe Thread Size, though these terms generally refer to similar standards. The primary function of NPS is to provide a uniform system for designating and measuring pipe sizes, facilitating compatibility and ease of use in plumbing, construction, and industrial settings.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-51676999d6498cdd7ba881a128f7d63f&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-5710fd22abab3effd14cb3f3d4187858&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-37388fa1515f3cf7a8930b2598d5740e&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-1d52749554047f9105f29ff3d1b53ac5&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-20a6e7f0600d773fff6396f54c63b132&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-711c2dd0d5dd4ddd0ed3c6d027a7e27c&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-d9d6f8ad3531ac0840bf5ba01dc89ab8&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-b5ae20c528cd11f1deab499df53ad378&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-57eadb61afc03dbca89ec4177318d30f&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-fe46a083e9b28534077cc616c7a8fcd2&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-40e7dd88714557fcaa5b58340393bd06</data>
      <data key="d4">ASME B16.5-2013.pdf</data>
      <data key="d5">1776329039</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
