    <node id="500">
      <data key="d0">500</data>
      <data key="d1">data</data>
      <data key="d2">500 is a numerical value representing a specific data point in the pressure-temperature ratings table. It is listed as a temperature point in degrees Celsius (500°C), which is also a temperature value in the table. Additionally, 500 serves as a nominal designation for a material and a pressure class in the same table. These descriptions collectively indicate that 500 is a significant value used in the context of pressure-temperature ratings, serving multiple roles including temperature representation, material designation, and pressure classification.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-e08aa81b5449d47c5a323ae8a58ce735&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-fb7c5babdbcd75bdf9752cd67bcadc21&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-3d70c5f8f778994cad7edb7ef10f4635&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-685be4db70f3b18d8a8fac56db2cfaa3&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-79c91ff40c85bc2676ba1a4dead29f2a&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-65a7f7e9599ea4d5c1cfc7d449c5a081&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-2879e8ce1f305f975a2bf33f2d701842&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-603423286a04ee8b6cbcba90c6a2736a&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-8320960a6b13ba4e9b766f5cfbdd1e80</data>
      <data key="d4">ASME B16.5-2013.pdf</data>
      <data key="d5">1776329040</data>
