    <node id="Class 400 Flanges">
      <data key="d0">Class 400 Flanges</data>
      <data key="d1">artifact</data>
      <data key="d2">Class 400 Flanges are a specific class of flanges with an even higher pressure rating than Class 300.&lt;SEP&gt;Class 400 Flanges are pipe flanges with specific dimensions as outlined in ASME B16.5-2013.&lt;SEP&gt;Class 400 Flanges are specifications for flanges used in industrial applications, detailed in ASME B16.5-2013.&lt;SEP&gt;Class 400 Flanges are a type of flange mentioned in the document.&lt;SEP&gt;Class 400 Flanges are described in the ASME B16.5-2013 standard, detailing their dimensions.&lt;SEP&gt;Class 400 Flanges are described in Table II-14 of the ASME B16.5-2013 standard.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-439097792cec97ce9b1b0fb080fa39fc&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-bbc4f25f5a21132e1571d8baa298136c&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-f67cfb71cad6bdaadc291b0dfadb7d87&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-e0e55f15f4fdc887c0046610b4244415&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-9ab03faa83213dbc994bff8e8951d1d7&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-71a674a140c79338fd271bcee63fa8e6</data>
