    <node id="650">
      <data key="d0">650</data>
      <data key="d1">data</data>
      <data key="d2">650 is a numerical value representing a specific data point in various contexts. It is primarily associated with a temperature value of 650°C, which is listed in the pressure-temperature ratings table. Additionally, 650 is also mentioned as a working pressure at 300°F in the same table. These descriptions indicate that 650 can refer to a temperature point or a data point in a series. The term 650 is used consistently across different entries to denote a specific temperature or pressure value in the pressure-temperature ratings table.</data>
