    <node id="750">
      <data key="d0">750</data>
      <data key="d1">data</data>
      <data key="d2">750 is a temperature value in degrees Celsius, specifically mentioned in a table and pressure-temperature ratings table. It also appears as a data point in a series. Additionally, 750 psi is the working pressure at 400°F for the 72Ni–15Cr–8Fe B564 Gr. N06600 material and represents a pressure value in pounds per square inch gauge (psig). While 750 is primarily associated with temperature, it is also used to denote pressure values in specific contexts.</data>
