    <node id="465°C">
      <data key="d0">465°C</data>
      <data key="d1">temperature</data>
      <data key="d2">465°C is a temperature threshold for certain materials, beyond which specific phase conversions may occur.&lt;SEP&gt;465°C is the temperature threshold above which the carbide phase of carbon–molybdenum steel may convert to graphite.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-a3453de580e274b0494108b0ff7189ee&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-fb7c5babdbcd75bdf9752cd67bcadc21&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-d88c25523fb6a395eb9e2724eb0719d5</data>
