    <node id="True Y">
      <data key="d0">True Y</data>
      <data key="d1">artifact</data>
      <data key="d2">True “Y” refers to a specific type of pipe fitting, often mentioned in the context of dimensions and specifications. It is a Y-shaped fitting used in piping systems, particularly for branching off from a main pipe. This fitting is described in the ASME B16.5-2013 standard, which specifies its configuration and usage. True “Y” is a type of flanged fitting, characterized by its 45-degree elbow design and its role in connecting three pipes at a single point. This configuration is crucial for ensuring proper flow and pressure distribution in various industrial and plumbing applications.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-02c8f43c223cee2154c66d0d4ab324af&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-87960735c6e595f042bd664132512ec0&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-c51efac4fa55567bbc6ceb90ad47bc5d&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-824f6bfcd2b200f81ced17dd1feea1ae&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-711c2dd0d5dd4ddd0ed3c6d027a7e27c&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-2cfed12e16e2f62a0ac34d806ce49eea&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-4313edccf5db74352d91e3f18890a0a0&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-5fd12d8684f80d487e4f8acfca82848a&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-bca2cf22c89695d4ce65335b23352b32&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-eb33e5534b0b007ab3fc536bdf30e65c&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-40e7dd88714557fcaa5b58340393bd06</data>
      <data key="d4">ASME B16.5-2013.pdf</data>
