      <data key="d1">material</data>
      <data key="d2">Carbon–molybdenum steel is a type of steel that may undergo phase conversion to graphite upon prolonged exposure to high temperatures.&lt;SEP&gt;Carbon–Molybdenum Steel is a type of steel that may undergo phase conversion to graphite at high temperatures.</data>
