    <node id="45-deg Elbow">
      <data key="d0">45-deg Elbow</data>
      <data key="d1">artifact</data>
      <data key="d2">45-deg Elbow refers to a specific type of pipe fitting that connects pipes at a 45-degree angle. This fitting is mentioned in various contexts, including dimensions and specifications, and is formally defined in the ASME B16.5-2013 standard. It is also known as a 45-degree elbow fitting, which is used in piping systems and has specific dimensions as detailed in relevant documents. The 45-deg Elbow is a type of flanged fitting that serves to connect pipes at a 45-degree angle, ensuring proper alignment and flow direction in piping systems.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-02c8f43c223cee2154c66d0d4ab324af&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-ccbc09bef8fd93e5314dec1dbec481cb&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-87960735c6e595f042bd664132512ec0&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-c51efac4fa55567bbc6ceb90ad47bc5d&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-824f6bfcd2b200f81ced17dd1feea1ae&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-2cfed12e16e2f62a0ac34d806ce49eea&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-eb33e5534b0b007ab3fc536bdf30e65c&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-40e7dd88714557fcaa5b58340393bd06</data>
      <data key="d4">ASME B16.5-2013.pdf</data>
      <data key="d5">1776329041</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="A240 Gr. 310H">
      <data key="d0">A240 Gr. 310H</data>
      <data key="d1">artifact</data>
      <data key="d2">A240 Gr. 310H is a type of material used in manufacturing, specifically a grade of steel.&lt;SEP&gt;A240 Gr. 310H is a specific grade of material with defined pressure-temperature ratings.&lt;SEP&gt;A240 Gr. 310H is a material designation used in forgings, castings, and plates.&lt;SEP&gt;A240 Gr. 310H is another material designation listed in the table.</data>
