      <data key="d0">Lapped Joint</data>
      <data key="d1">artifact</data>
      <data key="d2">A lapped joint is a type of pipe joint where the ends of two pipes are overlapped and secured together.&lt;SEP&gt;Lapped Joint is a type of joint for pipe flanges as detailed in ASME B16.5-2013.</data>
