      <data key="d5">1776329041</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Counterbore">
      <data key="d0">Counterbore</data>
      <data key="d1">artifact</data>
      <data key="d2">Counterbore is a feature in flanges where the back of the flange has a recessed area.&lt;SEP&gt;Counterbore is a recessed area in a pipe fitting that is larger than the bore.&lt;SEP&gt;Counterbore is a recessed area in a surface, typically to accommodate a bolt head or other fastener.&lt;SEP&gt;Counterbore is a recessed area around the hole in a flange where the bolt head sits flush with the flange surface.&lt;SEP&gt;Counterbore is a feature of the pipe flange that provides clearance for the bolt head as detailed in ASME B16.5-2013.&lt;SEP&gt;Counterbore is the recessed area around the bolt hole in the flange.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-5e85bee1a6414b667d34d9e3ddb49f16&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-de39ca8c7c360d8542b6e7b848f32671&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-ab71f5f8294a0ded93d84d65df8a8aeb&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-90c280892e81306b9d7b1a397e54f308&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-e253e99ebed9a87e642e60132b8f53d9&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-c5ace9ce39146c54679f4e19c3434a59</data>
      <data key="d4">ASME B16.5-2013.pdf</data>
      <data key="d5">1776329041</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
