    <node id="Taper">
      <data key="d0">Taper</data>
      <data key="d1">concept</data>
      <data key="d2">Taper is a dimension related to the hub of the flange, with a maximum angle of 7 degrees.&lt;SEP&gt;Taper refers to the maximum angle of 7 degrees for certain types of flanges.&lt;SEP&gt;Taper refers to the gradual reduction in diameter along the length of the hub, not exceeding 7 degrees.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-47d30b91c8304767d9ee5dee433bb6cd&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-de39ca8c7c360d8542b6e7b848f32671&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-27138329aa3769f926ca7ebbcd2c8891</data>
      <data key="d4">ASME B16.5-2013.pdf</data>
      <data key="d5">1776329042</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
