    <node id="Temp., °C">
      <data key="d0">Temp., °C</data>
      <data key="d1">concept</data>
      <data key="d2">Temp., °C is a category and column header in tables that represent temperature in degrees Celsius. This term is used to indicate the temperature at which pressure ratings are given or specified for various materials. Temp., °C measures temperature in degrees Celsius and is crucial for determining appropriate pressure ratings under specific temperature conditions.</data>
