    <node id="Ring Joint Groove">
      <data key="d0">Ring Joint Groove</data>
      <data key="d1">artifact</data>
      <data key="d2">Ring Joint Groove is a feature on a flange designed for sealing purposes. It is specifically a groove for a ring joint seal in pipe fittings and a component mentioned in various technical documents. The dimensions of the ring joint groove are detailed in Table II-5 of Mandatory Appendix II, indicating its importance in ensuring proper sealing. This feature is crucial for flanged fittings, requiring adherence to specific dimensions as outlined in the relevant specifications.</data>
