    <node id="Facings">
      <data key="d0">Facings</data>
      <data key="d1">concept</data>
      <data key="d2">Facings are the surfaces of pipe fittings that come into contact with other parts.&lt;SEP&gt;Facings are described in paragraph 6.4.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-1a18d7afa11aad3756a7707e009d78fc&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-57eadb61afc03dbca89ec4177318d30f</data>
      <data key="d4">ASME B16.5-2013.pdf</data>
      <data key="d5">1776329043</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Intersecting Centerlines">
      <data key="d0">Intersecting Centerlines</data>
      <data key="d1">concept</data>
      <data key="d2">Intersecting Centerlines are lines that cross each other in pipe fittings.&lt;SEP&gt;Intersecting centerlines are detailed in paragraph 6.2.4.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-1a18d7afa11aad3756a7707e009d78fc&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-57eadb61afc03dbca89ec4177318d30f</data>
      <data key="d4">ASME B16.5-2013.pdf</data>
      <data key="d5">1776329043</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Center-to-Base Face Dimension">
      <data key="d0">Center-to-Base Face Dimension</data>
      <data key="d1">concept</data>
      <data key="d2">Center-to-base face dimension R is the finished dimension and is detailed in paragraph 6.1.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-1a18d7afa11aad3756a7707e009d78fc</data>
      <data key="d4">ASME B16.5-2013.pdf</data>
      <data key="d5">1776329043</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Bases">
      <data key="d0">Bases</data>
      <data key="d1">artifact</data>
      <data key="d2">Bases are components of fittings and are intended for support in compression.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-1a18d7afa11aad3756a7707e009d78fc</data>
      <data key="d4">ASME B16.5-2013.pdf</data>
      <data key="d5">1776329043</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Reducers and Eccentric Reducers">
      <data key="d0">Reducers and Eccentric Reducers</data>
      <data key="d1">artifact</data>
      <data key="d2">Reducers and eccentric reducers are fittings that reduce pipe sizes and are detailed in paragraphs 6.2.3 and 6.4.2.2.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-1a18d7afa11aad3756a7707e009d78fc</data>
      <data key="d4">ASME B16.5-2013.pdf</data>
      <data key="d5">1776329043</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="End-to-End Dimensions">
      <data key="d0">End-to-End Dimensions</data>
      <data key="d1">concept</data>
      <data key="d2">End-to-end dimensions of reducers are calculated by adding the proper height to provide for ring joint groove applying to each flange.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-1a18d7afa11aad3756a7707e009d78fc</data>
      <data key="d4">ASME B16.5-2013.pdf</data>
      <data key="d5">1776329043</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="ASTM E29">
      <data key="d0">ASTM E29</data>
      <data key="d1">standard</data>
      <data key="d2">ASTM E29 is a standard defining conventions for rounding off numbers.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-d9d6f8ad3531ac0840bf5ba01dc89ab8</data>
      <data key="d4">ASME B16.5-2013.pdf</data>
      <data key="d5">1776329043</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="DN">
      <data key="d0">DN</data>
      <data key="d1">concept</data>
      <data key="d2">DN (Nominal Diameter) is a concept used in international standards to relate to NPS.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-d9d6f8ad3531ac0840bf5ba01dc89ab8</data>
      <data key="d4">ASME B16.5-2013.pdf</data>
      <data key="d5">1776329043</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="bolt">
      <data key="d0">bolt</data>
      <data key="d1">artifact</data>
      <data key="d2">Bolt is an artifact used in assembling flanged joints.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-d9d6f8ad3531ac0840bf5ba01dc89ab8</data>
      <data key="d4">ASME B16.5-2013.pdf</data>
      <data key="d5">1776329043</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="gasket">
      <data key="d0">gasket</data>
      <data key="d1">artifact</data>
      <data key="d2">Gasket is an artifact used in assembling flanged joints.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-d9d6f8ad3531ac0840bf5ba01dc89ab8</data>
      <data key="d4">ASME B16.5-2013.pdf</data>
      <data key="d5">1776329043</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="ASME PCC-1">
      <data key="d0">ASME PCC-1</data>
      <data key="d1">standard</data>
      <data key="d2">ASME PCC-1 is a standard describing special techniques such as controlled bolt tightening.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-d9d6f8ad3531ac0840bf5ba01dc89ab8&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-f024c3dde67312e25d76e977dcb7753c</data>
      <data key="d4">ASME B16.5-2013.pdf</data>
      <data key="d5">1776329043</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Dimensions of Class 300 Flanges">
      <data key="d0">Dimensions of Class 300 Flanges</data>
      <data key="d1">concept</data>
      <data key="d2">The Dimensions of Class 300 Flanges are listed in Tables 11 and 11 (Continued) of ASME B16.5-2013.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-4a2aa51a49817516d8e488a9d7c544a9</data>
      <data key="d4">ASME B16.5-2013.pdf</data>
      <data key="d5">1776329043</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Nominal Pipe Size (NPS)">
      <data key="d0">Nominal Pipe Size (NPS)</data>
      <data key="d1">concept</data>
      <data key="d2">Nominal Pipe Size (NPS) is a key parameter for specifying the size of the flanges in ASME B16.5-2013.&lt;SEP&gt;Nominal Pipe Size (NPS) is a measurement used to describe the size of pipes mentioned in the ASME B16.5-2013 standard.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-4a2aa51a49817516d8e488a9d7c544a9&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-1d0f7d26ba441435e49ef6d46820f716</data>
      <data key="d4">ASME B16.5-2013.pdf</data>
      <data key="d5">1776329043</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Bore Diameter">
      <data key="d0">Bore Diameter</data>
      <data key="d1">attribute</data>
      <data key="d2">Bore Diameter is a dimension of the flange described in ASME B16.5-2013.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-4a2aa51a49817516d8e488a9d7c544a9</data>
      <data key="d4">ASME B16.5-2013.pdf</data>
      <data key="d5">1776329043</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Through Hub Diameter">
      <data key="d0">Through Hub Diameter</data>
      <data key="d1">attribute</data>
      <data key="d2">Through Hub Diameter is a dimension of the flange described in ASME B16.5-2013.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-4a2aa51a49817516d8e488a9d7c544a9</data>
      <data key="d4">ASME B16.5-2013.pdf</data>
      <data key="d5">1776329043</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
