    </node>
    <node id="Threaded Flanges">
      <data key="d0">Threaded Flanges</data>
      <data key="d1">artifact</data>
      <data key="d2">Threaded Flanges are pipe flanges with threads for connection.&lt;SEP&gt;Threaded flanges are a type of flange where the connection is made through threading.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-de39ca8c7c360d8542b6e7b848f32671&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-803a0311f8fc78c3478b577229218993</data>
      <data key="d4">ASME B16.5-2013.pdf</data>
      <data key="d5">1776329043</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Slip-On Flanges">
      <data key="d0">Slip-On Flanges</data>
      <data key="d1">artifact</data>
      <data key="d2">Slip-On Flanges are pipe flanges that are attached to the pipe by slipping them over the end of the pipe and welding them in place.&lt;SEP&gt;Slip-on flanges are a type of flange where the pipe is slipped over the flange and held in place by welding.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-de39ca8c7c360d8542b6e7b848f32671&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-c5ace9ce39146c54679f4e19c3434a59</data>
      <data key="d4">ASME B16.5-2013.pdf</data>
      <data key="d5">1776329043</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Socket-Welding Flanges">
      <data key="d0">Socket-Welding Flanges</data>
      <data key="d1">artifact</data>
      <data key="d2">Socket-welding flanges are a type of flange where the pipe is inserted into a socket and welded in place.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-de39ca8c7c360d8542b6e7b848f32671</data>
      <data key="d4">ASME B16.5-2013.pdf</data>
      <data key="d5">1776329043</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Lapped Flanges">
      <data key="d0">Lapped Flanges</data>
      <data key="d1">artifact</data>
      <data key="d2">Lapped flanges are a type of flange where the pipe is lapped against the flange face.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-de39ca8c7c360d8542b6e7b848f32671</data>
      <data key="d4">ASME B16.5-2013.pdf</data>
      <data key="d5">1776329043</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Class 2500 Pipe Flanges">
      <data key="d0">Class 2500 Pipe Flanges</data>
      <data key="d1">artifact</data>
      <data key="d2">Class 2500 pipe flanges are a specific type of flange with a pressure rating of 2500 pounds per square inch.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-de39ca8c7c360d8542b6e7b848f32671</data>
      <data key="d4">ASME B16.5-2013.pdf</data>
      <data key="d5">1776329043</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Bolt Holes">
      <data key="d0">Bolt Holes</data>
      <data key="d1">artifact</data>
      <data key="d2">Bolt holes are the openings in the flange where bolts are inserted.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-de39ca8c7c360d8542b6e7b848f32671</data>
      <data key="d4">ASME B16.5-2013.pdf</data>
      <data key="d5">1776329043</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Male and Female">
      <data key="d0">Male and Female</data>
      <data key="d1">artifact</data>
      <data key="d2">Male and female flanges are a type of flange where one half has male threads and the other half has female threads.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-de39ca8c7c360d8542b6e7b848f32671</data>
      <data key="d4">ASME B16.5-2013.pdf</data>
      <data key="d5">1776329043</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Tongue and Groove">
      <data key="d0">Tongue and Groove</data>
      <data key="d1">artifact</data>
      <data key="d2">Tongue and Groove is a method of joining pipes where a tongue on one pipe fits into a groove on another.&lt;SEP&gt;Tongue and groove flanges are a type of flange where one half has a tongue and the other half has a groove.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-de39ca8c7c360d8542b6e7b848f32671&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-7d620a92f42ccd64b2c87242914a0398</data>
      <data key="d4">ASME B16.5-2013.pdf</data>
      <data key="d5">1776329043</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Point Height">
      <data key="d0">Point Height</data>
      <data key="d1">concept</data>
      <data key="d2">Point height is the distance from the bottom of the flange to the top of the points.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-de39ca8c7c360d8542b6e7b848f32671</data>
      <data key="d4">ASME B16.5-2013.pdf</data>
      <data key="d5">1776329043</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Stud Bolt">
      <data key="d0">Stud Bolt</data>
      <data key="d1">artifact</data>
      <data key="d2">Stud bolts are long bolts used to secure the flange to the pipe.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-de39ca8c7c360d8542b6e7b848f32671</data>
      <data key="d4">ASME B16.5-2013.pdf</data>
      <data key="d5">1776329043</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Height of Points">
      <data key="d0">Height of Points</data>
      <data key="d1">concept</data>
      <data key="d2">The height of points is the distance from the bottom of the flange to the top of the points.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-de39ca8c7c360d8542b6e7b848f32671</data>
      <data key="d4">ASME B16.5-2013.pdf</data>
      <data key="d5">1776329043</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Bolt Lengths">
      <data key="d0">Bolt Lengths</data>
      <data key="d1">concept</data>
      <data key="d2">Bolt lengths are the lengths of the bolts used to secure the flange.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-de39ca8c7c360d8542b6e7b848f32671</data>
      <data key="d4">ASME B16.5-2013.pdf</data>
      <data key="d5">1776329043</data>
      <data key="d6" />
