    <node id="Joint Leakage">
      <data key="d0">Joint Leakage</data>
      <data key="d1">concept</data>
      <data key="d2">Joint Leakage refers to the risk of fluid leakage at the connection points due to forces and moments developed in connected piping or equipment.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-925b39d264b455e6e2dfa9b4a8725e96</data>
      <data key="d4">ASME B16.5-2013.pdf</data>
      <data key="d5">1776329043</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Connected Piping Or Equipment">
      <data key="d0">Connected Piping Or Equipment</data>
      <data key="d1">artifact</data>
      <data key="d2">Connected Piping Or Equipment includes piping and equipment that are joined together and may develop forces and moments leading to joint leakage.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-925b39d264b455e6e2dfa9b4a8725e96</data>
      <data key="d4">ASME B16.5-2013.pdf</data>
      <data key="d5">1776329043</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Flanged Joints">
      <data key="d0">Flanged Joints</data>
      <data key="d1">artifact</data>
      <data key="d2">Flanged Joints are connections between pipes or equipment where the ends are fitted with flanges.&lt;SEP&gt;Flanged joints are covered by this standard and require specific bolting.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-925b39d264b455e6e2dfa9b4a8725e96&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-7f206c1ddea4cbeb2d1fc9d3ca987bee</data>
      <data key="d4">ASME B16.5-2013.pdf</data>
      <data key="d5">1776329043</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Thermal Gradients">
      <data key="d0">Thermal Gradients</data>
      <data key="d1">concept</data>
      <data key="d2">Thermal Gradients refer to temperature differences that can affect the performance of flanged joints.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-925b39d264b455e6e2dfa9b4a8725e96</data>
      <data key="d4">ASME B16.5-2013.pdf</data>
      <data key="d5">1776329043</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Gaskets">
      <data key="d0">Gaskets</data>
      <data key="d1">artifact</data>
      <data key="d2">Gaskets are sealing devices placed between flanges to prevent leaks.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-925b39d264b455e6e2dfa9b4a8725e96&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-28281081225db05b8b7d5f11501b022d</data>
      <data key="d4">ASME B16.5-2013.pdf</data>
      <data key="d5">1776329043</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Creep Range">
      <data key="d0">Creep Range</data>
      <data key="d1">concept</data>
      <data key="d2">Creep Range is a temperature range where materials exhibit creep, leading to decreasing bolt loads and potential joint leakage.&lt;SEP&gt;The creep range is considered to be at temperatures in excess of 370°C (700°F) for Group 1 materials.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-925b39d264b455e6e2dfa9b4a8725e96&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-30dae618425190cfb2b37b3fc339e4ee</data>
      <data key="d4">ASME B16.5-2013.pdf</data>
      <data key="d5">1776329043</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="High Temperature">
      <data key="d0">High Temperature</data>
      <data key="d1">concept</data>
      <data key="d2">High Temperature conditions can lead to decreasing bolt loads and potential joint leakage in flanged joints.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-925b39d264b455e6e2dfa9b4a8725e96</data>
      <data key="d4">ASME B16.5-2013.pdf</data>
      <data key="d5">1776329043</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Low Temperature">
      <data key="d0">Low Temperature</data>
      <data key="d1">concept</data>
      <data key="d2">Low Temperature conditions can affect the ductility of certain materials, potentially leading to shock loading and high stress concentration.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-925b39d264b455e6e2dfa9b4a8725e96</data>
      <data key="d4">ASME B16.5-2013.pdf</data>
      <data key="d5">1776329043</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="System Hydrostatic Testing">
      <data key="d0">System Hydrostatic Testing</data>
      <data key="d1">method</data>
      <data key="d2">System Hydrostatic Testing involves applying pressure to flanged joints to check their integrity.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-925b39d264b455e6e2dfa9b4a8725e96</data>
      <data key="d4">ASME B16.5-2013.pdf</data>
      <data key="d5">1776329043</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Hub Thickness">
      <data key="d0">Hub Thickness</data>
      <data key="d1">concept</data>
      <data key="d2">Hub Thickness is the thickness of the hub in welding neck flanges, which affects the joint's ability to sustain loads.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-925b39d264b455e6e2dfa9b4a8725e96</data>
      <data key="d4">ASME B16.5-2013.pdf</data>
      <data key="d5">1776329043</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Weld End Dimensional Requirements">
      <data key="d0">Weld End Dimensional Requirements</data>
      <data key="d1">method</data>
      <data key="d2">Weld End Dimensional Requirements specify the dimensions needed for proper welding of flanges.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-925b39d264b455e6e2dfa9b4a8725e96</data>
      <data key="d4">ASME B16.5-2013.pdf</data>
      <data key="d5">1776329043</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Attachment Welds">
      <data key="d0">Attachment Welds</data>
      <data key="d1">artifact</data>
      <data key="d2">Attachment Welds are welds made to attach flanges to pipes or equipment.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-925b39d264b455e6e2dfa9b4a8725e96</data>
      <data key="d4">ASME B16.5-2013.pdf</data>
      <data key="d5">1776329043</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
