    <node id="Outside Diameter">
      <data key="d0">Outside Diameter</data>
      <data key="d1">concept</data>
      <data key="d2">Outside Diameter is a dimension measurement for pipe fittings and specifically describes the external diameter of a pipe or pipe fitting. This dimension is crucial for identifying the correct size of pipe flanges and is detailed in the ASME B16.5-2013 standard. It is also referenced in tables for Class 900 Flanges and is used to specify the nominal pipe size. Outside Diameter refers to the external circumference of the pipe or fitting, making it an essential parameter for ensuring proper fit and compatibility in piping systems.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-5e85bee1a6414b667d34d9e3ddb49f16&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-bc5fbf3f97e8bcfd2b79a4ca1deaa326&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-e27122e3377c1128b67882eafcae8b01&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-4a2aa51a49817516d8e488a9d7c544a9&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-f17e2ea5f154e082324b9ac9b148a73e&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-90c280892e81306b9d7b1a397e54f308&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-5fd12d8684f80d487e4f8acfca82848a&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-bca2cf22c89695d4ce65335b23352b32</data>
      <data key="d4">ASME B16.5-2013.pdf</data>
      <data key="d5">1776329045</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
