    <node id="Working Pressures by Classes, bar">
      <data key="d0">Working Pressures by Classes, bar</data>
      <data key="d1">category</data>
      <data key="d2">Working pressures by classes, measured in bar, are specifications for materials under different temperature conditions. These pressure ratings are categorized for various temperature classes and material groups, providing detailed pressure data by class in the table. The term "Working Pressures by Classes, bar" refers to the pressure ratings for different temperature classes of materials used in pressure vessels and piping systems. This information is organized into tables that list working pressures for different temperature ranges and material groups, ensuring comprehensive coverage of pressure specifications across various conditions.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-94e58312a7e84066f13cc4e7ad9465d9&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-b16d82598801637712b84cc1424040fd&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-c38d97b0aceca7464ebbbd9a7db0c8d9&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-5c8a2582fdf55b244cf7d4892e61cc9f&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-82774a230daae46ca5bfd3f0231302b9&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-2879e8ce1f305f975a2bf33f2d701842&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-30fa107e1afe5b6cba81caa3af7a1ab4&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-d6b3a683ba2b5f6743c1c3f349ed79b5&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-8a7f9dd013cfda7208dab84e4831ce4a</data>
