    </edge>
    <edge source="Ring Joint Flange" target="Minimum Flange Thickness, tf">
      <data key="d7">1.0</data>
      <data key="d8">Ring Joint Flanges require sufficient thickness added to the minimum flange thickness, tf, so that the bottom of the ring joint groove is in the same plane as the flange edge of a full thickness flange.</data>
      <data key="d9">flange specification,thickness requirement</data>
      <data key="d10">chunk-43e5005d4928be252c7355587c71a1aa</data>
      <data key="d11">ASME B16.5-2013.pdf</data>
      <data key="d12">1776329066</data>
      <data key="d13" />
    </edge>
    <edge source="Tongue and Groove Flange" target="Minimum Flange Thickness, tf">
      <data key="d7">1.0</data>
      <data key="d8">For Tongue and Groove Flanges, the thickness of the lap remaining after machining the tongue or groove face is no less than the nominal wall thickness of the pipe used.</data>
      <data key="d9">flange specification,thickness requirement</data>
      <data key="d10">chunk-43e5005d4928be252c7355587c71a1aa</data>
      <data key="d11">ASME B16.5-2013.pdf</data>
      <data key="d12">1776329066</data>
      <data key="d13" />
    </edge>
    <edge source="Minimum Flange Thickness, tf" target="Large Male and Female Flange">
      <data key="d7">1.0</data>
      <data key="d8">For Large Male and Female Flanges, the finished height of the male face is the greater of the wall thickness of the pipe used or 7 mm (0.25 in.), and the thickness of the lap remaining after machining the female face is no less than the nominal wall thickness of the pipe used.</data>
      <data key="d9">flange specification,thickness requirement</data>
      <data key="d10">chunk-43e5005d4928be252c7355587c71a1aa</data>
      <data key="d11">ASME B16.5-2013.pdf</data>
      <data key="d12">1776329066</data>
      <data key="d13" />
    </edge>
